12 years have not seen Saddam lesson his throat hold on his people. he continues to be a disruptive influence on affairs in the middle east. in an oil based economy, this instability causes economic turmoil world wide. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://india39.com/inspectors.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
In America, our leaders hold power not through threat of torture, military force, or rite of birth. they hold power due to a political system which, on the surface, lets the populous give power to the leaders. througout history, presidents and congress has held power through the economic success of the country.  in the face of economic failure, presidents look outward for ways to rally the public.  so, here is a way to accomplish (possibly) several tasks, each important, but not important enough to wage war individually.  in no particular order:<br>
<br>
- economic reasons<br>
- anti-terrorism<br>
- end the saddam regime, and free iraq <br>
- institute a pro-american(pro-western) government into iraq<br>
- stabilize the middle east<br>
- economic reasons<br>
<br>
<br>
anyway, i wholly support our president, and our troops overseas, and wish them a speedy victory. i may not totally agree with the decision to go to war, but i DO support our governmental system. i wont always agree with every decision they make, but, I am happy they are making decisions.<br>
<br>
now, if the french support us, or dont, i really dont care. after all, going to war without the french, is like going deer hunting without an accordian..<br>
<br>
