<br>
Do you have any idea how many hundreds of thousands of innocent people Saddam has killed?  Have you ever been there?  Have you ever been anywhere in the Arab world?  If the answer is no, than what exactly is it that you think makes you qualified to express your comments on the matter?  Rest assured that for every Iraqi soldier that has bought into Saddam's regime, there are 100 more who welcome the Americans.  Understand that violence is necessary, to prevent exponentially MORE violence in the future.  <br>
<br>
Iraq not a threat?  Ask the British about the ricin in London, that was traced DIRECTLY back to Al-Qaeda operatives operating in Northern Iraq.  After you ask, try to convince yourself that a totalitarian megalomaniac like Saddam *really* didn't know they were there, despite the fact that he was funneling money and weapons to them to fight the Kurds.  Now ask yourself whether those same Al-Qaeda operatives were connected to the ones that flew the 9/11 flights.  I'm sure they would NEVER have even considered using any of those neurotoxins against the American people.  No sir, they're harmless.  <br>
<br>
You seeing the big picture yet?    <br>
