the frustrating part is that i dont wholly agree with the WAR. but i cant stand idiots who protest at military bases, factorys, or places that have NO IMPACT WHATSOEVER on the political decision to go to war.  here, in america, we value our rights to make asses of ourselves. to openly protest the war, or any decision made by our government.<br>
<br>
but if your going to protest, protest the WAR, not the WARRIOR.  whenever i see soldiers going to work in domestic bases, having to drive though hordes of protesters, it makes me want to puke. go to your state government building. write letters to your congressmen, or make a million man march on washington/whitehouse to get your points across.. but dont target those americans who are doing what they are told, in service to thier country. I dont know how many of you have actually pulled the trigger to kill another man, but i can tell you it is a serious thing. getting your rifle, is all cool and @#%$, and its neat to show army pictures to your buddies,  but when your there, looking down the sights at your &quot;enemy&quot;, a man, just like you, who may have family, may not.. someone who, a few weeks earlier, or a few weeks later might be a drinking buddy, a peer, or just some dude on the street in a country you didnt know existed a month before.... all bullshit aside.. anyway, you dont pull the trigger because of oil. you dont end his life because of economics. you kill that soldier because that is what soldiers do. and if you dont, he will kill you. its not an easy thing to do, or to live with. and when you are overseas doing that, the LAST thing you want in the back of your mind, is some antiwar @#%$ harassing your family, your friends, or your place of work.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sylpheden>Sylpheden</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#628CBC>(4/7/03 1:08:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=548.topic&index=85>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> hmmm just when did i protest the warriors?? <br>
