<br>
The difference is, the French wait to be invited, they respect the sovereignty of the nation involved.  They may certainly play fast and loose with local laws, but they've never violated international law (not and got caught, anyway).  When they sunk the Rainbow Warrior it was done by intelligence agents who were tried and convicted under kiwi law, not by a missle from a French warship.<br>
<br>
There are ways to do these things and unilateral invasion ain't it.  We can't just allow countries to invade each other because the other guy's president has a silly mustache.  We're slipping back into the bad old days of nationalism and constant warfare that we were finally forced to put aside by the threat of global nuclear war. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sarion81>Sarion81</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blackburrow Trainee</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#628CBC>(4/7/03 5:47:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=548.topic&index=96>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> Well, I wish I had more time but I gotta run to class, damn lab...<br>
